---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { CONTACT_EMAIL } from '../lib/seo';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Use — inbrowser.sh"
  description="Terms of use for inbrowser.sh, a free collection of client-side developer tools."
  path="/terms"
>
  <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 pt-10 pb-16 prose-tool">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Terms of Use</h1>
    <p>
      inbrowser.sh provides free, browser-based developer utilities. By using the site, you agree to use the
      tools responsibly and to verify outputs before relying on them in production systems.
    </p>

    <h2>Client-side tools</h2>
    <p>
      Tool logic runs in your browser. We do not guarantee that every output is suitable for every use case,
      and you are responsible for reviewing generated IDs, hashes, encoded text, QR codes, converted data,
      and other results before use.
    </p>

    <h2>No professional advice</h2>
    <p>
      inbrowser.sh is a developer productivity site. It does not provide legal, security, financial, compliance,
      or professional advice.
    </p>

    <h2>Acceptable use</h2>
    <p>
      Do not use inbrowser.sh to attack, disrupt, scrape aggressively, reverse engineer protected systems, or
      process data that you are not authorized to handle.
    </p>

    <h2>Availability</h2>
    <p>
      The site is provided as-is and may change, move, or be unavailable without notice.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Questions about these terms can be sent to
      <a class="text-accent" href={`mailto:${CONTACT_EMAIL}`}>{CONTACT_EMAIL}</a>.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
